snippet.textDisplay:
I have to object to some of the lyrics of this song. Ali (R.A) is from the Ahle Bayt and one of the greatest companions of the Prophet (s.a.w). But we do not take his status beyond that. We do not give him super-human status.

We need to understand hadiths in context. Using phrases of hadith in songs is also disrespectful.

Before im branded a wahabi, let me clarify that im no wahabi. i have a lot of objections with what they say. We need to stick to a middle path on these issues, or there is a great chance of being misguided.

The superlative praise is what led to Jesus being considered as Son of God, and the worship of saints in Christianity. We obviously are not there yet, nor intend to be, but we should be careful. If not us, someone else would take things a bit too far. And we know people throughout Islamic history,  who have taken things too far.

We can tone it down a little bit.
